WEBVTT

00:14.188 --> 01:06.675
♪♪

01:06.675 --> 01:09.330
Kayla,
are you seeing this?

01:09.330 --> 01:11.593
Whatever.

01:11.593 --> 01:14.422
It's pretty spectacular.

01:14.422 --> 01:16.293
Wow.

01:16.293 --> 01:18.600
Those mountains
are gorgeous.

01:36.879 --> 01:38.141
[Glass breaking]

01:38.141 --> 01:40.709
[Tires screeching]

01:43.059 --> 01:48.108
[Heavy breathing]

01:50.806 --> 01:53.548
Malik:
They converted this massive
old church off of 20th Street

01:53.548 --> 01:57.595
into this, like, insane,
just, dreamland.

01:57.595 --> 02:00.381
There was dancers hanging
from the rafters and glitter

02:00.381 --> 02:02.948
just like exploding
from the ceilings.

02:02.948 --> 02:06.038
There was boys and girls
and club kids and queens

02:06.038 --> 02:07.953
and everything in between,
you name it.

02:07.953 --> 02:12.175
And so it's my first night
there, and I see this guy

02:12.175 --> 02:16.223
and he's like this, like,
perfect Adonis,

02:16.223 --> 02:20.531
just like flowing blonde hair
and sculpted abs,

02:20.531 --> 02:21.793
and just, like, a
total Greek statue.

02:21.793 --> 02:23.534
Wait, so you were
in your 20s?

02:23.534 --> 02:24.796
Uh-huh.

02:24.796 --> 02:27.712
And I was terrified.

02:27.712 --> 02:28.974
He turned out to be
a total prick,

02:28.974 --> 02:31.716
but your first one
usually is.

02:31.716 --> 02:34.589
Actually,
most of them are.

02:34.589 --> 02:36.199
Everyone except your dad.

02:38.941 --> 02:43.163
Aaron, what's up?
-Do you guys hear that?

02:43.163 --> 02:44.773
No, what?

02:44.773 --> 02:51.997
♪♪

02:51.997 --> 02:53.608
I don't hear anything.

02:53.608 --> 02:58.961
♪♪

02:58.961 --> 03:00.876
Exactly.

03:00.876 --> 03:03.270
No traffic, no sirens,
no shouting.

03:03.270 --> 03:06.011
I think it's the most
beautiful sound I've ever heard.

03:06.011 --> 03:08.144
Well, you know what they
say about silence right, Dad?

03:08.144 --> 03:10.320
-What?
-It's deafening.

03:10.320 --> 03:11.843
How original.

03:11.843 --> 03:14.977
I think she means
it's peaceful.

03:14.977 --> 03:17.327
So what about you, Dad?

03:17.327 --> 03:19.329
What?

03:19.329 --> 03:22.463
How'd you lose your virginity,
was it with Mom?

03:22.463 --> 03:24.116
It was.

03:24.116 --> 03:25.553
I was about 100 years old,

03:25.553 --> 03:27.859
which is how old you'll be
when you lose yours.

03:27.859 --> 03:29.252
How do you know
I haven't lost it already?

03:29.252 --> 03:30.819
Ok, booger.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.951
Dinners over, you're done.

03:32.951 --> 03:34.562
No.

03:37.565 --> 03:39.393
Malik:
You know, it's just because
of her mom, right?

03:39.393 --> 03:42.265
She's feeling abandoned.

03:42.265 --> 03:43.484
Let's just give her
some time.

03:43.484 --> 03:44.746
She'll stop blaming you
soon enough

03:44.746 --> 03:46.182
and when school starts
up again,

03:46.182 --> 03:49.664
she'll be busy like
totally being a senior.

03:49.664 --> 03:51.970
Yeah.

03:51.970 --> 03:55.887
Yeah,
maybe you're right.

03:55.887 --> 03:57.237
She'll be like
the cool new kid.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.151
Yeah, exactly,
she'll be fine.

03:59.151 --> 04:01.632
She'll be better then fine,
she'll be too legit to quit,

04:01.632 --> 04:04.113
that's what all the cool kids
are saying, right?

04:04.113 --> 04:07.725
I-I don't know.

04:07.725 --> 04:09.553
I'm the old man,
remember?

04:09.553 --> 04:12.295
You're the New York
party monster.

04:16.081 --> 04:19.519
Come on, baby, you know I burned
all those brain cells years ago.

04:22.043 --> 04:23.611
Don't burn anymore.

04:29.878 --> 04:31.401
You really have
to start tomorrow?

04:31.401 --> 04:34.404
Mm-hmm.
You know I do.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.540
Can't afford to take
another day off.

04:46.416 --> 04:50.899
[Crickets chirping]

04:50.899 --> 04:59.168
♪♪

05:21.625 --> 05:23.105
Yo.

05:23.105 --> 05:24.411
Rise and shine, booger.

05:24.411 --> 05:25.803
It's your first day
in paradise.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.849
Screw off.

05:27.849 --> 05:29.546
Come on, your dad's
already left to work.

05:29.546 --> 05:31.940
Let's surprise him and get
this palace put together.

05:31.940 --> 05:34.856
-No.
-Come on, kid, get up.

05:34.856 --> 05:36.466
No.

05:36.466 --> 06:21.511
♪♪

06:21.511 --> 06:22.730
Malik:
I look good though,
right?

06:22.730 --> 06:24.079
[Both laugh]

06:24.079 --> 06:26.603
Oh, my God.
Yeah, that's hilarious.

06:26.603 --> 06:27.996
What'd you use
for your tits?

06:27.996 --> 06:32.566
Um, socks, obviously,
stuffed with rice, duh.

06:32.566 --> 06:37.440
You think that ones good,
check that out.

06:37.440 --> 06:40.791
Wait, oh, my God!
Is that my dad?

06:40.791 --> 06:42.924
Ah.
She's such a pretty girl.

06:42.924 --> 06:44.578
Oh, my...
No, no.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.362
She's hideous.
-What?

06:46.362 --> 06:50.018
Unh-unh, honey, this is not
hideous. This is punk rock.

06:50.018 --> 06:51.672
Oh, my God. It's my dad
in a dress.

06:51.672 --> 06:54.762
It's not punk rock.
-Oh, booger.

06:54.762 --> 06:57.025
Believe me, choosing to live
your life loud and proud

06:57.025 --> 06:59.593
is about the bravest thing
you can do in this world.

06:59.593 --> 07:38.109
♪♪

07:42.679 --> 07:44.376
Hey, how's it going?

07:44.376 --> 07:48.511
[Bird cawing]

07:58.739 --> 08:02.133
<i>-This sucks, Kayla.
-Yeah, I know.</i>

08:02.133 --> 08:04.919
Derek: <i>You might as well be
in another country.</i>

08:04.919 --> 08:06.224
Kayla:
Don't say that.

08:06.224 --> 08:08.183
You know I don't want
to be here.

08:08.183 --> 08:10.141
[Door knocking]

08:10.141 --> 08:12.187
-Hey.
-Learn to knock, Dad.

08:12.187 --> 08:13.580
I did knock.

08:13.580 --> 08:15.364
Well, you have to wait
for an answer.

08:15.364 --> 08:16.757
Derek: <i>
Hey, Mr. Miller.</i>

08:16.757 --> 08:18.628
<i>How you liking
the small town life?</i>

08:18.628 --> 08:20.717
Hey, Derek.
How's it going?

08:20.717 --> 08:22.371
<i>Doing my best.</i>

08:22.371 --> 08:24.504
<i>City's not the same
without your daughter, though.</i>

08:24.504 --> 08:27.855
Oh, well, you guys will be
together soon enough.

08:27.855 --> 08:30.161
I'm sure of that.

08:33.207 --> 08:34.991
Hey, Derek.

08:34.991 --> 08:36.645
I'm going to get murdered
if I stay in this room

08:36.645 --> 08:40.389
any longer so um, we'll catch up
later, okay, dude?

08:40.389 --> 08:41.738
<i>Sounds good,
Mr. Miller.</i>

08:41.738 --> 08:44.959
Alright, I'm going.

08:48.832 --> 08:53.184
<i>-How's your other dad doing?
He's fine, I guess.</i>

08:55.665 --> 08:59.234
<i>Just do me a favor, Kayla, and
I don't mean anything by this,</i>

08:59.234 --> 09:03.194
<i>but just, don't share
any drinks with them, okay?</i>

09:03.194 --> 09:05.196
All men are created equal.

09:05.196 --> 09:06.633
They are endowed
by their creator

09:06.633 --> 09:09.026
with certain
unalienable rights,

09:09.026 --> 09:11.072
that among these
are life, liberty,

09:11.072 --> 09:12.682
and the pursuit of happiness.

09:16.512 --> 09:18.558
Hey, how's it coming?

09:20.690 --> 09:23.563
Slow.

09:23.563 --> 09:25.216
This guy's the worst.

09:27.741 --> 09:30.221
Honestly, I just can't believe
I'm still taking on spec work.

09:30.221 --> 09:32.397
It won't be for long.

09:32.397 --> 09:36.401
I've seen enough of your writing
to know how brilliant you are.

09:36.401 --> 09:39.622
Get to work.

09:39.622 --> 09:42.016
I need some help paying off
this damn house.

09:42.016 --> 09:49.414
[Heavy sigh]
Okay.

09:51.286 --> 10:00.295
[Banging in the distance]

10:03.994 --> 10:15.702
[Banging continues]

10:32.588 --> 11:29.993
♪♪

11:29.993 --> 11:34.041
[Banging]

11:34.041 --> 12:16.170
♪♪

12:26.528 --> 12:28.312
[Door knock]

12:31.011 --> 12:32.403
-Good morning.
-Hi there.

12:32.403 --> 12:34.754
Hi, I'm Tiffany
you're new neighbor.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.843
Oh, oh, hi.
I'm Aaron.

12:36.843 --> 12:38.366
Sorry to come by so early,

12:38.366 --> 12:40.498
I just, I saw your gardener
working so I figured

12:40.498 --> 12:42.239
I'd come say hi.

12:42.239 --> 12:44.241
My gardener?

12:44.241 --> 12:47.462
Uh, I -- Oh, oh, no,
that, he's not.

12:47.462 --> 12:49.856
He's my um,
my partner.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.118
Malik.
-Oh.

12:51.118 --> 12:52.467
Come say hi.

12:52.467 --> 12:54.817
This is Tiffany,
our next door neighbor.

12:56.688 --> 12:57.951
-Hi.
-Wow.

12:57.951 --> 13:01.084
That's so exciting.

13:01.084 --> 13:03.260
We don't have any
of you in town.

13:03.260 --> 13:06.002
Really, none, huh?

13:06.002 --> 13:07.525
Maybe they're just all
in hiding.

13:07.525 --> 13:10.267
[Nervous laughter]

13:10.267 --> 13:12.792
Anyway, I brought
over a housewarming gift.

13:12.792 --> 13:16.360
When it blooms, it's just --
it's stunning.

13:16.360 --> 13:20.060
Okay. Thank you. That's,
that's really, we didn't --

13:20.060 --> 13:21.975
Oh, don't worry about it.

13:21.975 --> 13:25.630
I'm just so happy we have some
fresh faces in the neighborhood.

13:25.630 --> 13:27.632
Nothing ever changes
around here.

13:27.632 --> 13:28.982
Well, that's sounds like
just the kind of change

13:28.982 --> 13:31.114
we're looking for.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.768
I better get going,
I just...

13:32.768 --> 13:34.901
Yeah, it was so good
to meet you.

13:34.901 --> 13:37.294
Bye bye.

13:37.294 --> 13:38.643
She seems nice.

13:38.643 --> 13:39.862
Mm.
She's something.

13:39.862 --> 13:42.212
This is, uh...

13:42.212 --> 13:43.823
Okay.
Well, I gotta go.

13:48.436 --> 13:50.177
[Printer printing]

13:50.177 --> 13:52.005
What you doing,booger?

13:52.005 --> 13:53.833
Kayla:
Printing resumes.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.444
I'm gonna go crazy if I'm stuck
inside with you every day.

13:56.444 --> 13:59.099
So sweet of you, Kayla.
Thank you.

13:59.099 --> 14:00.622
And here I was kinda hoping
you'd stick around

14:00.622 --> 14:02.624
and be my assistant.

14:02.624 --> 14:05.670
Oh, yeah, what you going to
pay me with, my dad's money?

14:05.670 --> 14:08.804
Excuse you, I have
my own money, thank you.

14:08.804 --> 14:11.851
Yeah, right.

14:11.851 --> 14:13.635
Let's hope I don't end up
on a milk carton.

14:13.635 --> 14:17.204
Okay, your dad and I
won't miss you if you do.

14:21.251 --> 14:37.267
♪♪

14:37.267 --> 14:38.834
Man: <i>It was through
my wife and loving children</i>

14:38.834 --> 14:42.098
<i>I realized what
American values really were.</i>

14:42.098 --> 14:43.534
<i>It's not our personal pride</i>

14:43.534 --> 14:45.667
<i>or what we achieve
as individuals</i>

14:45.667 --> 14:47.625
<i>that makes this country great.</i>

14:47.625 --> 14:53.718
<i>It's our ability as a family to
maintain and uphold our values.</i>

14:53.718 --> 14:57.200
<i>The traditional family unit.</i>

14:57.200 --> 14:58.854
<i>It's everything.</i>

15:05.687 --> 15:09.169
<i>The traditional family unit.</i>

15:09.169 --> 15:10.779
<i>It's everything.</i>

15:15.262 --> 15:43.116
♪♪

15:43.116 --> 15:46.858
The traditional family unit.

15:46.858 --> 15:48.469
It's everything.

15:53.430 --> 15:55.084
Kayla?

16:12.275 --> 16:24.809
♪♪

16:30.293 --> 16:33.905
I did not realize
we were painting.

16:33.905 --> 16:39.607
Yeah, figured it could
use a fresh coat.

16:39.607 --> 16:42.653
Look's great.

16:42.653 --> 16:44.742
What'd you get
up to today?

16:44.742 --> 16:49.834
Oh, my God. What did
you get up to today?

16:49.834 --> 16:52.620
Oh, you know,
I hung out.

16:52.620 --> 16:55.318
Unpacked a few things.
Got a job.

16:55.318 --> 16:56.667
Shut up!

16:56.667 --> 16:59.322
Yeah, for real,
all by herself.

16:59.322 --> 17:00.976
-What?
-Whoo.

17:00.976 --> 17:02.238
You're looking at
the new hostess

17:02.238 --> 17:03.848
at Bill and Pete's
Bar and Grill.

17:03.848 --> 17:08.592
Oh, my God, totally
celebrating that.

17:08.592 --> 17:09.984
You're getting up.

17:12.291 --> 17:19.820
♪♪

17:19.820 --> 17:21.692
♪ Why you look so blue ♪

17:21.692 --> 17:23.128
♪ Boy, I know it's true ♪

17:23.128 --> 17:27.436
♪ You do
You do ♪

17:27.436 --> 17:29.222
♪ Come on to the floor ♪

17:29.222 --> 17:31.180
♪ There's room for one more ♪

17:31.180 --> 17:33.052
♪ And that's you ♪
-No.

17:33.052 --> 17:35.054
♪ Yeah, you ♪

17:35.054 --> 17:38.013
♪ Yeah, we got all the kids who
got nothing to lose ♪

17:38.013 --> 17:40.798
Malik, you're missing out,
get up here.

17:40.798 --> 17:43.192
Malik, get over here.

17:43.192 --> 17:46.195
♪♪

17:46.195 --> 17:47.849
Oh!

17:47.849 --> 17:51.766
♪♪

17:51.766 --> 17:55.117
♪ Here's looking at you ♪

17:55.117 --> 18:08.609
♪♪

18:08.609 --> 18:15.442
[Keyboard tapping]

18:38.421 --> 18:45.907
♪♪

18:45.907 --> 18:48.649
[Telephone rings]

18:48.649 --> 18:50.825
Malik: Do you remember
when we were kids?

18:50.825 --> 18:53.480
That summer we stayed up
at your aunt's cottage

18:53.480 --> 18:55.351
and you thought it was a
good idea to tell your friend

18:55.351 --> 18:56.961
Erica about us?

18:56.961 --> 18:58.746
And you remember how I said

18:58.746 --> 19:00.487
I had a really bad
feeling about it.

19:00.487 --> 19:02.924
Liam: <i>Except the world's
a different place, Malik.</i>

19:02.924 --> 19:04.186
<i>It's not like
it was back then.</i>

19:04.186 --> 19:05.405
Oh, my God,
how can you say that

19:05.405 --> 19:07.146
and actually even believe
yourself?

19:07.146 --> 19:09.060
Someone just broke into my house
and spray painted the word --

19:09.060 --> 19:10.366
<i>Okay, don't --
don't say it.</i>

19:10.366 --> 19:12.151
<i>I hate that world.</i>

19:12.151 --> 19:14.065
Well, my point is the world
is exactly

19:14.065 --> 19:15.632
the same place
as it was back then.

19:15.632 --> 19:17.025
People don't change,
Liam,

19:17.025 --> 19:18.940
they just get better
at hiding how they feel.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.334
<i>I know you don't mean
that Malik.</i>

19:21.334 --> 19:23.162
<i>What does Aaron
think about it all?</i>

19:23.162 --> 19:24.989
He thinks
the same as me.

19:24.989 --> 19:27.775
<i>You haven't told him
yet, have you?</i>

19:27.775 --> 19:30.212
<i>You just had a security
system installed,</i>

19:30.212 --> 19:32.301
<i>Malik, what's he going
to say about that?</i>

19:32.301 --> 19:34.651
I don't know.
I don't know.

19:34.651 --> 19:37.001
<i>Okay. Whatever.
It's your life.</i>

19:37.001 --> 19:38.481
<i>You do what you want.</i>

19:38.481 --> 19:40.353
[Garage door opens]

19:40.353 --> 19:41.832
Shit, I gotta go.

19:45.923 --> 19:47.186
-Oh, hi.
-Hey.

19:47.186 --> 19:48.709
What are you
doing in here?

19:48.709 --> 19:51.799
Just putting away some boxes.
How was your day?

19:51.799 --> 19:54.236
-So long.
-Mhm.

19:54.236 --> 19:56.325
Can you please hurry up
and get famous already

19:56.325 --> 19:58.458
so I can retire?

19:58.458 --> 20:00.677
Maybe in a million years.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.853
Confidence, that's great.

20:02.853 --> 20:05.204
I knew there was a reason
I fell so hard for you.

20:05.204 --> 20:07.031
[Laughs]

20:11.688 --> 20:13.342
I'm so glad you guys
could make it.

20:13.342 --> 20:15.344
Well, thanks so much
for inviting us.

20:15.344 --> 20:17.781
Marshall.

20:17.781 --> 20:19.827
These are our neighbors
I told you about.

20:19.827 --> 20:21.698
-Hi, there.
-Hey.

20:21.698 --> 20:23.222
-Hi, I'm Aaron.
-Aaron, welcome.

20:23.222 --> 20:24.962
-This is Malik.
-Malik, welcome.

20:24.962 --> 20:26.616
Thank you.
Hi.

20:26.616 --> 20:28.488
So, Malik, it seems
that you and I have

20:28.488 --> 20:29.750
a little something
in common.

20:29.750 --> 20:31.055
Oh, yeah.
What's that?

20:31.055 --> 20:32.753
Well, we both stay
at home all day

20:32.753 --> 20:36.844
while our significant others
venture out into the real world.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.367
[Laughter]

20:38.367 --> 20:42.415
I run an IT company
from the house.

20:42.415 --> 20:45.766
I work alone. I'm a one-man
show, but I love it.

20:45.766 --> 20:47.376
♪♪

20:47.376 --> 20:49.378
Oh, yeah, I bumped into
Tiffany on my way home

20:49.378 --> 20:53.469
from work the other day.
I mentioned you're a writer.

20:53.469 --> 20:55.602
A writer.
That's so exciting,

20:55.602 --> 20:57.734
So what are you working on?

20:57.734 --> 21:01.651
I mean,
it's just a bio piece.

21:01.651 --> 21:03.784
Just ghost writing.

21:03.784 --> 21:06.656
-Well, to new neighbors.
-New neighbors.

21:06.656 --> 21:08.179
New neighbors.

21:08.179 --> 21:09.790
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

21:09.790 --> 21:23.804
♪♪

21:23.804 --> 21:30.289
[Banging]

21:34.945 --> 22:15.377
♪♪

22:15.377 --> 22:22.166
[Alarm blaring]

22:22.166 --> 22:25.126
Hey!
Stop!

22:25.126 --> 22:26.606
Don't hurt me!

22:26.606 --> 22:30.218
What the hell are you doing
on my property?

22:30.218 --> 22:32.829
Take this.
Please take it.

22:32.829 --> 22:37.486
Take it.
Take it.

22:37.486 --> 22:39.532
Don't tell anyone.

22:39.532 --> 22:42.926
♪♪

22:42.926 --> 22:45.059
Aaron: What the fuck?
What's going on?

22:45.059 --> 22:46.408
Is everything all right?

22:46.408 --> 22:50.194
Do you know where
I put my keys?

22:50.194 --> 22:52.066
I get so confused lately.

22:52.066 --> 22:54.764
[Alarm blaring]

22:54.764 --> 23:01.336
I, uh, my sense of time
is, uh, mixed up these days.

23:01.336 --> 23:02.598
Aaron: A security system.

23:02.598 --> 23:04.034
We didn't
even have one in Chicago.

23:04.034 --> 23:06.210
Jesus fucking.

23:06.210 --> 23:08.038
I said I'm sorry, okay.
I should have asked.

23:08.038 --> 23:11.390
I'm sorry.
-How much did this thing cost?

23:11.390 --> 23:15.176
-Like a few thousand.
-Oh, my God.

23:15.176 --> 23:17.047
You know what people do
in the suburbs,

23:17.047 --> 23:18.658
they leave
their doors unlocked.

23:18.658 --> 24:13.277
♪♪

24:13.277 --> 24:15.541
Man: <i>Don't tell anyone.</i>

24:15.541 --> 24:18.152
♪♪

24:18.152 --> 24:19.632
<i>Please take it.</i>

24:19.632 --> 24:26.203
♪♪

24:29.163 --> 24:30.556
Aaron:
Everything all right?

24:32.427 --> 24:35.952
Yeah.

24:35.952 --> 24:37.693
Well, it's nice
to see you, too.

24:37.693 --> 24:43.917
♪♪

24:43.917 --> 24:46.615
You call the alarm
company today?

24:46.615 --> 24:50.271
-For what?
-A refund.

24:50.271 --> 24:51.838
We're not
keeping that thing.

24:59.628 --> 25:02.849
So is this what you do
in this town?

25:02.849 --> 25:04.503
Pretty much.

25:11.684 --> 25:15.296
So you're the new girl
with the two dads, right?

25:15.296 --> 25:16.819
Here we go again.

25:16.819 --> 25:19.126
No, I didn't mean it
like that.

25:19.126 --> 25:21.171
I think it's pretty cool.

25:25.741 --> 25:27.613
So where's your mom?

25:27.613 --> 25:28.918
You're nosey.

25:28.918 --> 25:31.007
Just want to get to know
you is all.

25:31.007 --> 25:33.749
She's probably partying
in Costa Rica

25:33.749 --> 25:36.796
with her new family
and my inheritance.

25:36.796 --> 25:39.668
Ouch.

25:39.668 --> 25:41.365
You really want
to get to know me?

25:43.977 --> 25:45.369
Get to know this.

25:46.501 --> 25:49.330
Shit.
No way!

25:49.330 --> 25:51.027
-I just crushed you.
-Okay, rematch.

25:51.027 --> 25:52.507
We're doing this
again.

25:58.252 --> 27:26.340
♪♪

27:26.340 --> 27:32.259
[Heavy breathing]

27:44.053 --> 27:47.927
Hi.

27:47.927 --> 27:50.538
Good God.
Is he?

27:52.845 --> 27:57.327
Aaron, last night I -- I think
I saw something over there,

27:57.327 --> 27:59.503
there was --
-Tragic, isn't it?

27:59.503 --> 28:01.375
Yeah, do you know
what happened?

28:01.375 --> 28:04.770
Well, his grandson found him
in the middle of the night.

28:04.770 --> 28:08.643
Called a few of us
over to say our goodbyes.

28:08.643 --> 28:11.907
Turned into a bit
of a celebration.

28:11.907 --> 28:14.344
It's just
so sad for him.

28:14.344 --> 28:15.998
They were really close.

28:15.998 --> 28:43.460
♪♪

28:43.460 --> 28:48.465
[Door creaks open]

28:48.465 --> 30:04.280
♪♪

30:04.280 --> 30:06.848
[Door opens, closes]

30:06.848 --> 30:35.137
♪♪

30:35.137 --> 30:38.967
[Engine Revs]

30:38.967 --> 30:41.927
Need a lift?

30:41.927 --> 30:43.406
Are you stalking
me now?

30:43.406 --> 30:46.714
Pretty much.

30:46.714 --> 30:48.629
Where you going?

30:48.629 --> 30:51.284
I'm heading to work.

30:51.284 --> 30:52.981
Call in sick.

30:52.981 --> 30:54.374
[Laughs]
No way.

30:54.374 --> 30:56.332
Come on.

30:56.332 --> 30:57.899
Please?

30:57.899 --> 31:00.380
♪♪

31:00.380 --> 31:02.556
You just don't
give up do you?

31:02.556 --> 31:04.297
♪♪

31:04.297 --> 31:06.777
You ever think
about leaving?

31:06.777 --> 31:08.475
I don't think so.

31:08.475 --> 31:10.999
I mean,
everything's here.

31:10.999 --> 31:13.175
My friends, my family.

31:15.656 --> 31:17.310
You.

31:20.226 --> 31:25.013
I have a boyfriend
back in the city.

31:25.013 --> 31:26.885
I mean, at least I think
I still do.

31:30.323 --> 31:32.325
You should probably
figure that out.

31:32.325 --> 31:42.683
♪♪

31:42.683 --> 31:44.250
Hey, do you see that?

31:50.560 --> 31:52.171
What is he doing?

31:52.171 --> 31:57.089
♪♪

31:57.089 --> 31:58.438
Come on, let's
get out of here.

31:58.438 --> 32:09.057
♪♪

32:10.363 --> 32:13.061
-[Groans]
-What is it?

32:13.061 --> 32:14.584
Nothing.

32:14.584 --> 32:18.545
What?
What is it?

32:18.545 --> 32:20.460
Just look -- I just really
don't want to go over there,

32:20.460 --> 32:21.722
those people creep me out.

32:21.722 --> 32:23.376
Oh, my God.
You always do this.

32:23.376 --> 32:24.899
Do what?

32:24.899 --> 32:26.596
Every time we try to make
friends that are bit more,

32:26.596 --> 32:28.903
like, normal,
you create drama.

32:28.903 --> 32:30.470
What does normal mean?

32:30.470 --> 32:31.775
You know what it means.

32:31.775 --> 32:33.516
[Laughs]

32:33.516 --> 32:36.476
Okay, what's the world
for an "Uncle Tom,"

32:36.476 --> 32:38.565
but for gay people?

32:40.915 --> 32:43.309
Really?

32:45.354 --> 32:47.313
[Sighs]

32:47.313 --> 32:49.315
Tiffany: Well, I don't care
what anybody says

32:49.315 --> 32:51.534
it doesn't matter
if you're a single mother

32:51.534 --> 32:56.104
or a married couple like us,
or -- or even, you know.

32:56.104 --> 32:58.280
Love is all that matters.

32:58.280 --> 33:00.108
I mean, that's a really nice
thought and everything,

33:00.108 --> 33:03.242
but I'm not sure most people
would actually agree with that.

33:03.242 --> 33:06.245
Well, people who don't
are assholes.

33:06.245 --> 33:07.507
Honey.

33:07.507 --> 33:09.422
Well, come on, honey,
they are.

33:09.422 --> 33:10.814
No, he's right.

33:10.814 --> 33:12.599
Even my ex-wife showed
her true colors.

33:12.599 --> 33:14.296
You wouldn't believe
how many times I had to hear

33:14.296 --> 33:17.212
her lawyers try and educate me
on how being gay meant

33:17.212 --> 33:18.953
I was fit to parent
my own daughter.

33:18.953 --> 33:22.043
Hm, Yeah, I believe
the official term

33:22.043 --> 33:24.872
they used to describe our
relationship was "illegitimate."

33:24.872 --> 33:28.354
That's right. High risk, that
was one of my favorites.

33:28.354 --> 33:31.966
You know
what high risk means.

33:31.966 --> 33:33.228
What?

33:35.187 --> 33:38.146
Oh, Jesus.

33:38.146 --> 33:41.019
I-I find it disgusting
how easy it is

33:41.019 --> 33:45.501
for false stereotypes
to shape public opinion.

33:45.501 --> 33:49.853
People don't think anymore,
they follow.

33:49.853 --> 33:51.159
Tyler, is that you?

33:51.159 --> 33:53.335
Yeah, sorry I missed dinner.

33:53.335 --> 33:55.033
It's in the fridge, honey.

33:55.033 --> 34:00.473
-So, where were you, son?
-Just out, with a new friend.

34:00.473 --> 34:01.996
How did it go?

34:01.996 --> 34:04.477
Very well,
thanks, Mom.

34:04.477 --> 34:07.001
I'll be in my room.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.568
Seems like a good kid.

34:08.568 --> 34:11.397
Well, he's a teenager,
does that count?

34:11.397 --> 34:15.139
[Laughter]

34:18.491 --> 34:21.623
Did you say the second door
or the third?

34:21.623 --> 34:23.277
Marshall: Alright, who's ready
for apple crumble?

34:26.498 --> 34:29.763
[Door creaks open]

34:29.763 --> 35:09.368
♪♪

35:09.368 --> 35:11.500
1792.

35:11.500 --> 35:14.721
♪♪

35:14.721 --> 35:18.028
I see you found Richard.

35:18.028 --> 35:22.032
He was my great,
great something or other.

35:22.032 --> 35:26.341
Apparently quite a ship's mate.
He fought for the blue coats.

35:26.341 --> 35:29.301
I could have sworn you said it
was the third door on the right.

35:29.301 --> 35:31.912
Second,
but who's counting?

35:34.219 --> 35:36.264
You can really see
the family resemblance.

35:36.264 --> 35:39.093
Well, a long blood line.

35:39.093 --> 35:42.488
I started gathering info on our
lineage over a decade ago

35:42.488 --> 35:45.795
and I've got a solid
collection of photos now.

35:48.320 --> 35:52.150
Come on, let me point you
in the right direction.

36:03.857 --> 36:15.173
♪♪

36:20.830 --> 36:27.054
[Floor creaking]

36:27.141 --> 36:29.535
Man: <i>
It became my duty to help them.</i>

36:29.535 --> 36:33.103
<i>To lead them back to
a wholesome existence</i>

36:33.103 --> 36:37.673
<i>where they can find happiness
and reclaim their identity.</i>

36:37.673 --> 36:42.635
<i>These young men and women,
they're suffering inside.</i>

36:42.635 --> 37:31.423
♪♪

37:31.423 --> 37:33.425
[Glass breaking]

37:33.425 --> 37:37.080
[Heavy breathing]

37:37.080 --> 37:40.562
Man: <i>During a time of racism
and homophobia</i>

37:40.562 --> 37:42.477
<i>my father was a maverick.</i>

37:42.477 --> 37:44.827
<i>An American hero.</i>

37:47.917 --> 37:52.226
♪♪

37:52.226 --> 37:54.228
I thought your ass
got a job.

37:54.228 --> 37:57.492
It's part time, duh.

37:57.492 --> 37:59.451
Make sure not to
strain yourself too hard.

37:59.451 --> 38:01.453
I'm not stupid,
thanks.

38:01.453 --> 38:13.943
♪♪

38:13.943 --> 38:15.989
I got you.

38:15.989 --> 38:18.296
Hey, you look
freezing.

38:18.296 --> 38:23.910
♪♪

38:23.910 --> 38:25.477
Thank you.

38:25.477 --> 38:31.613
[Wind whistling]

38:33.093 --> 38:35.530
Come on,
let's go smoke a bowl.

38:35.530 --> 38:37.227
Yeah.

38:37.227 --> 38:38.751
[Door knocking]

38:47.194 --> 38:51.590
Hi, it's Malik,
right?

38:51.590 --> 38:56.116
Listen, I --
I need to talk to you.

38:56.116 --> 38:57.683
It's about my grandpa.

38:59.859 --> 39:01.469
Please.

39:03.645 --> 39:09.042
I'm sorry if he startled you
in your back yard.

39:09.042 --> 39:14.221
His mind,
it wasn't well.

39:14.221 --> 39:19.182
But did he say what he was
doing out there?

39:23.796 --> 39:26.015
Honestly, your guess
is as good as mine.

39:29.584 --> 39:32.544
Did he
give you anything?

39:32.544 --> 39:34.154
No.

39:34.589 --> 39:38.419
♪♪

39:38.419 --> 39:39.986
Why?

39:39.986 --> 39:44.382
♪♪

39:44.382 --> 39:46.384
They're calling it
a suicide,

39:46.384 --> 39:51.040
saying that he took
all his medication at once.

39:51.040 --> 39:57.220
I miss him.
[Sobbing]

39:57.220 --> 39:58.918
It's okay.

39:58.918 --> 40:05.446
♪♪

40:05.446 --> 40:08.057
I miss him so much.

40:08.057 --> 40:12.235
Uh, I didn't realize
we had company.

40:14.847 --> 40:16.239
Uh, Aaron, this is uh --

40:16.239 --> 40:19.852
I'm Matthew. Hi, it's nice
to finally meet you.

40:19.852 --> 40:21.114
You're Aaron, right?

40:21.114 --> 40:22.724
That's right.

40:25.074 --> 40:27.076
Uh, well,
I should probably go.

40:27.076 --> 40:28.643
Thank you for listening.

40:28.643 --> 40:38.566
♪♪

40:38.566 --> 40:44.746
So, you obviously
like him.

40:44.746 --> 40:46.226
Who?

40:46.226 --> 40:47.923
Matthew.

40:47.923 --> 40:50.273
It's been a while since
we played with someone.

40:53.668 --> 40:57.280
Could be fun.
-Are you serious?

41:00.545 --> 41:02.372
Do you remember
when you dragged me

41:02.372 --> 41:05.941
to that party at
your friends Jason's?

41:05.941 --> 41:07.508
Could be like that.

41:10.816 --> 41:15.255
It's never gonna happen.
I only want you.

41:27.267 --> 41:30.400
Come here.

41:30.400 --> 41:36.929
[Screaming]

41:36.929 --> 41:38.583
Oh, my God.

41:38.583 --> 41:40.019
-Kayla.
-Oh, my God.

41:40.019 --> 41:41.847
I'm bleeding.
-Kayla, honey what is it?

41:41.847 --> 41:43.501
-Ah!
-Look at me!

41:43.501 --> 41:45.633
What happened, from where?
-I don't know.

41:49.463 --> 41:51.204
Where's it coming from?
What is it?

41:51.204 --> 41:53.119
-I don't know.
-Malik, get towels!

41:53.119 --> 41:56.078
♪♪

41:56.078 --> 41:57.471
Oh, my God.

41:57.471 --> 42:33.594
♪♪

42:33.594 --> 42:37.206
Do you think someone
put those up there?

42:37.206 --> 42:39.948
What?

42:39.948 --> 42:42.690
No.
Why would anyone do that?

42:42.690 --> 42:44.997
Probably just
living up there

42:44.997 --> 42:47.173
and they ate poison
or something and died.

42:47.173 --> 42:51.612
♪♪

42:51.612 --> 42:53.179
God, that's so much blood.

42:53.179 --> 43:20.119
♪♪

43:20.119 --> 43:21.947
Man: <i>That's why I founded
the Ernie Darrylson clinic,</i>

43:21.947 --> 43:23.601
<i>in my father's name.</i>

43:23.601 --> 43:26.299
<i>The clinic, you see, it offers
a path back</i>

43:26.299 --> 43:30.825
<i>towards righteousness,
away from sin and temptation.</i>

43:30.825 --> 43:36.483
<i>These young men and woman,
they're suffering inside.</i>

43:36.483 --> 43:38.093
<i>It became my --</i>

43:38.093 --> 43:41.488
♪♪

43:41.488 --> 43:43.751
<i>That's why I founded
the Ernie Darrylson clinic,</i>

43:43.751 --> 43:45.318
<i>in my father's name.</i>

43:45.318 --> 43:52.238
♪♪

43:52.238 --> 43:54.240
Malik: Gay conversion
therapy works.

43:54.240 --> 43:58.940
♪♪

43:58.940 --> 44:00.899
Jesus Christ.

44:03.510 --> 44:06.252
Kayla: Have you guys
seen my Polaroid blanks?

44:06.252 --> 44:08.471
I swear I had
a bunch of them.

44:08.471 --> 44:10.473
Aaron:
Maybe if you cleaned your room
once in a while.

44:10.473 --> 44:11.953
Nice try.

44:11.953 --> 44:31.016
♪♪

44:33.975 --> 44:36.108
<i>Don't tell anyone.</i>

44:37.283 --> 44:38.850
<i>Please take it.</i>

44:38.850 --> 44:55.040
♪♪

45:01.524 --> 45:04.658
Malik: I need
to tell you something.

45:04.658 --> 45:06.268
-What?
-I can't do it.

45:06.268 --> 45:08.923
Aaron:
What are you talking about?

45:08.923 --> 45:10.446
The book.

45:10.446 --> 45:12.840
My hard drive failed.
it's totally fried,

45:12.840 --> 45:14.320
last night
it started smoking.

45:14.320 --> 45:17.671
I just --
-Well, did you back it up?

45:20.456 --> 45:22.458
Oh, my God.

45:22.458 --> 45:25.113
[Door pounding]

45:25.113 --> 45:28.595
Malik, you've been in there
for almost an hour.

45:28.595 --> 45:30.249
You're using up
all the hot water.

45:30.249 --> 45:31.554
I have to go.

45:31.554 --> 45:35.776
♪♪

45:35.776 --> 45:38.213
Sorry, booger, I'll be out
in just a...

45:38.213 --> 47:12.264
♪♪

47:12.264 --> 47:14.962
Malik: Police are calling it
a murder suicide.

47:14.962 --> 47:23.841
♪♪

47:23.841 --> 47:26.234
Oh, my God.

47:26.234 --> 47:29.368
♪♪

47:29.368 --> 47:30.978
Is everything all right?

47:30.978 --> 47:36.288
♪♪

47:36.288 --> 47:38.943
-We need to move.
-Oh, God, here we go.

47:38.943 --> 47:40.466
We need to get out
of this town, Aaron,

47:40.466 --> 47:43.338
there's something
not right about this place.

47:43.338 --> 47:46.037
What are
you talking about?

47:46.037 --> 47:48.039
The night the alarm went
of Mr. Reinhart,

47:48.039 --> 47:50.693
he gave me a piece of paper.

47:50.693 --> 47:52.043
There's a series
of dates on it.

47:52.043 --> 47:55.263
It goes back
for decades.

47:55.263 --> 47:58.876
Will you just listen to me.
He was trying to warn us.

47:58.876 --> 48:01.617
I saw them in his house,
Aaron,

48:01.617 --> 48:03.054
Marshall and Matthew
and a bunch of them

48:03.054 --> 48:04.620
and they were doing
something in there,

48:04.620 --> 48:06.405
and the next day Reinhart,
he just turns up dead?

48:06.405 --> 48:07.667
I just --

48:07.667 --> 48:09.103
There was
another couple, Aaron.

48:09.103 --> 48:10.626
There was a gay couple
that lived in town

48:10.626 --> 48:12.933
and they were killed
10 years ago.

48:12.933 --> 48:14.195
Why the fuck wouldn't

48:14.195 --> 48:15.501
Marshall and Tiffany
have mentioned this?

48:15.501 --> 48:17.155
They knew and they
didn't say anything.

48:17.155 --> 48:18.417
They've been lying to us.

48:18.417 --> 48:22.029
Nobody's lying to us,
Mal.

48:22.029 --> 48:25.206
If you engaged with them.
If you literally spent any time

48:25.206 --> 48:27.730
at all being social with them,
you would know this.

48:29.776 --> 48:31.734
They were close with them.

48:31.734 --> 48:35.173
They told me all of this.

48:35.173 --> 48:37.262
Marshall and Tiffany
are good people, Mal,

48:37.262 --> 48:39.655
and you know what,
I happen to like this town.

48:39.655 --> 48:41.353
Jesus Christ, Aaron.

48:41.353 --> 48:43.833
You need to stop thinking that
everyone's trying to get you

48:43.833 --> 48:45.748
all the time.

48:45.748 --> 48:47.794
I thought
we were past this.

48:51.798 --> 48:55.323
What happened to you,
was tragic, I know, but --

48:55.323 --> 48:57.064
Oh, God, please.

49:01.416 --> 49:03.897
It's not going to happen
again, I promise.

49:03.897 --> 49:08.902
♪♪

49:08.902 --> 49:11.122
You can't make
that kind of promise.

49:11.122 --> 49:13.907
♪♪

49:13.907 --> 49:15.953
Liam: <i>
Malik, calm down, you're just
seeing what you want to see.</i>

49:15.953 --> 49:18.520
<i>The numbers are just noise,
they're meaningless.</i>

49:18.520 --> 49:20.174
Every 10 years,

49:20.174 --> 49:22.655
you don't think that's even like
a little bit strange?

49:22.655 --> 49:26.311
Liam: <i>
Do you think maybe, the reason
you keep calling me</i>

49:26.311 --> 49:30.750
<i>is because you're looking
for permission?</i>

49:30.750 --> 49:33.971
Permission for what?

49:33.971 --> 49:35.755
Liam: <i>To move on.</i>

49:35.755 --> 49:37.539
I have moved on, okay?

49:37.539 --> 49:40.542
I've clearly moved on.

49:40.542 --> 49:42.370
Liam: <i>We can't keep doing this,
Malik.</i>

49:42.370 --> 49:43.981
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>

49:43.981 --> 49:46.940
What? No, Liam, come on,
I need your help with this.

49:46.940 --> 49:50.639
Liam?
Shit.

49:50.639 --> 51:37.442
♪♪

51:37.442 --> 51:41.228
Malik: This happened to us
our first week living there.

51:41.228 --> 52:12.172
♪♪

52:21.268 --> 52:27.883
[Door creaks open]

52:29.276 --> 52:30.930
Malik: Hello?

52:30.930 --> 52:38.851
[Floor creaking]

52:49.992 --> 52:51.646
Hello?

52:57.261 --> 53:02.614
[Door creaks open]

53:07.575 --> 53:18.282
♪♪

53:18.282 --> 53:19.892
Hello?

53:30.555 --> 53:32.209
Who's there?

53:39.172 --> 54:12.858
♪♪

54:12.858 --> 54:14.686
What the fuck?

54:14.686 --> 54:17.079
♪♪

54:17.079 --> 54:18.559
Aaron!

54:18.559 --> 54:20.648
Why was my hard drive removed?

54:34.706 --> 54:36.273
What is this?

54:38.579 --> 54:40.451
This isn't me.

54:40.451 --> 54:42.279
Aaron, I swear
this didn't happen.

54:42.279 --> 54:45.020
They look
pretty real to me.

54:45.020 --> 54:46.805
Don't you see
what's going on?

54:46.805 --> 54:48.502
They're doing this to us.

54:48.502 --> 54:50.635
Why didn't you tell me
that this is what you wanted?

54:50.635 --> 54:52.767
I would have let you.

54:52.767 --> 54:55.248
It didn't happen.

54:55.248 --> 54:57.119
It's not.
Aaron, don't go.

54:57.119 --> 54:58.773
Stop.

55:00.819 --> 55:02.777
I don't.

55:02.777 --> 55:06.215
I don't want to see you here
when I get back.

55:06.215 --> 55:08.522
Where am
I supposed to go?

55:08.522 --> 55:09.784
Figure it out.

55:09.784 --> 55:12.265
Aaron!

55:12.265 --> 55:20.882
♪♪

55:20.882 --> 55:27.106
[Telephone ringing]

55:27.106 --> 55:30.849
[Crying]
Fuck.

55:30.849 --> 55:58.006
♪♪

55:58.006 --> 56:04.230
[Telephone ringing]

56:04.230 --> 56:05.753
Malik: Aaron, you have
to let me explain.

56:05.753 --> 56:07.625
What?

56:07.625 --> 56:10.454
Wait, what did she do?

56:14.849 --> 56:20.202
[Police radio chatter]

56:39.570 --> 56:42.964
She deserved it.
Jessica's a total bitch.

56:42.964 --> 56:45.402
Kayla, seriously, I do
not want to hear it.

56:45.402 --> 56:48.405
She said I was going
to give Tyler AIDs

56:48.405 --> 56:50.494
because, well, you know.

56:54.672 --> 56:58.415
People see your dad and I
as different than them,

56:58.415 --> 57:00.721
and different
scares people.

57:00.721 --> 57:02.984
Well, people are idiots.

57:02.984 --> 57:04.595
Plus, Tyler likes
me way better.

57:04.595 --> 57:07.467
I am fucking serious
right now, Kayla.

57:07.467 --> 57:09.730
In this town
and in this country,

57:09.730 --> 57:12.907
it is not safe for people
that stand out, okay?

57:12.907 --> 57:14.213
You need to forget
everything that I said

57:14.213 --> 57:15.475
about loud and proud,

57:15.475 --> 57:17.695
do not draw attention
to yourself.

57:17.695 --> 57:22.569
Don't speak out,
don't speak up, it is not safe.

57:22.569 --> 57:27.226
♪♪

57:27.226 --> 57:29.315
Besides, that Tyler kid
is a little creep.

57:29.315 --> 57:32.623
He only wants one thing
from you anyway.

57:32.623 --> 57:35.408
I don't want you hanging
out with him.

57:35.408 --> 57:39.281
Do you hear me?

57:39.281 --> 57:40.805
Kayla, do you hear me?

57:40.805 --> 57:44.461
Yeah, I hear you.

57:46.637 --> 57:48.116
Promise.

57:48.116 --> 57:54.209
♪♪

57:54.209 --> 57:57.691
Don't worry about Jessica.
We're done.

57:57.691 --> 57:59.476
I want to be with you.

57:59.476 --> 58:07.135
♪♪

58:07.135 --> 58:08.920
Wait.
Hold on a second.

58:08.920 --> 58:16.971
♪♪

58:16.971 --> 58:19.452
I've never gone
all the way before.

58:21.498 --> 58:24.283
Thanks for telling me.

58:24.283 --> 58:26.851
I'm ready though.

58:26.851 --> 58:29.854
No, that's okay.

58:29.854 --> 58:31.464
I think we should wait.

58:31.464 --> 58:36.991
♪♪

58:36.991 --> 58:38.558
What's wrong?

58:38.558 --> 58:42.693
♪♪

58:42.693 --> 58:44.172
You don't want me?

58:44.172 --> 58:47.132
No, no I do.

58:47.132 --> 58:49.830
I really do.

58:49.830 --> 58:53.965
Just, I want it
to be special.

58:53.965 --> 59:04.541
♪♪

59:04.541 --> 59:10.285
Man: <i>This, my friends,
this is radical feminism.</i>

59:10.285 --> 59:12.853
<i>The agenda that Clinton
and Clinton</i>

59:12.853 --> 59:15.464
<i>would impose on America.</i>

59:15.464 --> 59:20.295
<i>Abortion on demand, a litmus
test for the Supreme Court.</i>

59:20.295 --> 59:23.211
<i>Discrimination against
religious schools,</i>

59:23.211 --> 59:27.128
<i>women in combat units,
homosexual rights,</i>

59:27.128 --> 59:30.784
<i>but that's not the kind
of change America needs.</i>

59:30.784 --> 59:33.570
<i>It's not the kind of change
America wants,</i>

59:33.570 --> 59:35.310
<i>and its not the kind of change</i>

59:35.310 --> 59:39.576
<i>we can abide in a nation
we still call God's country.</i>

59:39.576 --> 01:00:32.324
♪♪

01:00:32.324 --> 01:00:34.674
[Doorbell rings]

01:00:38.460 --> 01:00:40.811
Malik.

01:00:40.811 --> 01:00:42.682
Can I help you
with something?

01:00:42.682 --> 01:00:46.991
-I could use a drink.
-Cheer up.

01:00:46.991 --> 01:00:49.297
I'm sure Aaron
will come around.

01:00:53.301 --> 01:00:57.088
Just doesn't
make any sense.

01:00:57.088 --> 01:00:58.959
So it's not true then?

01:01:01.179 --> 01:01:03.485
I'm not judging.

01:01:03.485 --> 01:01:07.054
No, it isn't true.

01:01:07.054 --> 01:01:10.667
At least
I don't think it is.

01:01:10.667 --> 01:01:13.974
You don't <i>think</i> it is.

01:01:13.974 --> 01:01:17.456
Things have just been...

01:01:17.456 --> 01:01:19.545
They've just been
a bit foggy lately.

01:01:25.420 --> 01:01:28.728
So, your hard drive.

01:01:28.728 --> 01:01:31.209
It's funny, Aaron
seemed so worry about it

01:01:31.209 --> 01:01:32.993
when I swung by the house
to pick it up

01:01:32.993 --> 01:01:36.301
but there was
nothing wrong with it.

01:01:36.301 --> 01:01:38.738
-Nothing.
-No.

01:01:38.738 --> 01:01:41.349
Nothing.

01:01:41.349 --> 01:01:46.833
There was something
else though.

01:01:46.833 --> 01:01:51.969
Malik, I,
I saw the folder.

01:01:51.969 --> 01:01:54.362
What folder?

01:01:54.362 --> 01:01:58.802
Well, I think
you know which one.

01:01:58.802 --> 01:02:01.369
If people were to catch wind
of that stuff,

01:02:01.369 --> 01:02:02.980
I mean, it just --
it wouldn't look good,

01:02:02.980 --> 01:02:06.157
especially someone
in your standing.

01:02:06.157 --> 01:02:07.462
I have no clue
what you're talking --

01:02:07.462 --> 01:02:10.248
We're friends,
Malik.

01:02:13.686 --> 01:02:16.950
Your secret
is safe with me.

01:02:16.950 --> 01:02:21.041
But if I were you, I really
would consider getting some help

01:02:21.041 --> 01:02:25.959
because you obviously
have a problem.

01:02:25.959 --> 01:02:29.615
I made you a back-up hard
drive over there

01:02:32.923 --> 01:02:36.230
I'll come by later
and install it.

01:02:36.230 --> 01:02:45.674
♪♪

01:02:45.674 --> 01:02:50.027
It's an exciting time
to be alive, Malik.

01:02:50.027 --> 01:02:53.857
So much change happening
in the world, yet so much

01:02:53.857 --> 01:02:58.252
seems to just stay the same,
do you know what I mean?

01:03:00.385 --> 01:03:04.389
Excuse me.
I have to go.

01:03:04.389 --> 01:04:06.973
♪♪

01:04:06.973 --> 01:04:15.982
[Light flickering]

01:04:15.982 --> 01:04:47.100
♪♪

01:04:47.100 --> 01:04:48.928
Liam, are you there?

01:04:48.928 --> 01:04:50.799
Operator: <i>Your call cannot be
completed as dialed.</i>

01:04:50.799 --> 01:04:52.627
<i>Check the number
and dial again.</i>

01:04:52.627 --> 01:05:03.725
♪♪

01:05:03.725 --> 01:05:07.425
[Gravely voice whispering]

01:05:07.425 --> 01:05:23.310
♪♪

01:05:23.310 --> 01:05:25.138
Woman:
Did you find your keys?

01:05:25.138 --> 01:05:28.315
Man: Okay, yeah.
Oh, I found them.

01:05:28.315 --> 01:05:31.492
They're right here.
-Oh, thank God.

01:05:31.492 --> 01:05:42.677
♪♪

01:05:42.677 --> 01:05:48.118
[Sobbing]

01:05:49.032 --> 01:05:52.122
Woman:
And here we are in our first day
in our new house.

01:05:52.122 --> 01:05:55.821
Let's get a shot of Sam's
new bike.

01:05:55.821 --> 01:05:59.216
-We're going to be happy here.
-Yeah.

01:05:59.216 --> 01:06:03.568
Hannah documented everything
that happened to her family.

01:06:03.568 --> 01:06:08.094
Well, at least they told us
how they really felt.

01:06:08.094 --> 01:06:11.184
Fuck you,
whoever did this.

01:06:11.184 --> 01:06:13.056
It's all the same things.

01:06:13.056 --> 01:06:15.188
Look at this,
he's giving camera tips.

01:06:15.188 --> 01:06:16.929
It's part of some
kind of ritual.

01:06:16.929 --> 01:06:19.453
Every 10 years, they make a
selection, that's --

01:06:19.453 --> 01:06:23.501
Aaron: <i>
Please, please do not say what
I think you're about to say.</i>

01:06:23.501 --> 01:06:26.591
-We're the selection. <i>
-Okay, don't, don't.</i>

01:06:26.591 --> 01:06:27.896
We've been chosen.

01:06:27.896 --> 01:06:31.988
[Laughter]

01:06:31.988 --> 01:06:34.816
<i>-Chosen for what?
-Once the selection's been made,</i>

01:06:34.816 --> 01:06:40.561
there's nothing anyone
can do to stop it.

01:06:40.561 --> 01:06:52.617
♪♪

01:06:52.617 --> 01:06:59.667
Aaron: <i>Malik?
Malik? You need help.</i>

01:06:59.667 --> 01:07:04.585
[High pitched squealing]

01:07:04.585 --> 01:07:06.370
Malik: Fuck.

01:07:06.370 --> 01:07:39.229
♪♪

01:07:39.229 --> 01:07:41.796
Oh, motherfuck.

01:07:43.233 --> 01:07:45.061
They switched my fucking meds.

01:07:45.061 --> 01:07:46.584
Operator: <i>This number has been
disconnected or is</i>

01:07:46.584 --> 01:07:48.368
<i>no longer in service.
-Liam, are you here?</i>

01:07:48.368 --> 01:07:50.414
<i>If you feel you have reached
this recording in error,</i>

01:07:50.414 --> 01:07:51.763
<i>please check the number and try
again.</i>

01:07:51.763 --> 01:07:54.635
Mom, please stop recording me.
I suck.

01:07:54.635 --> 01:07:57.769
Woman: Oh, come on, you're
getting really good.

01:07:57.769 --> 01:08:04.471
[Recorder playing]

01:08:04.471 --> 01:08:14.742
♪♪

01:08:14.742 --> 01:08:16.743
[Laughs]
I'm terrible.

01:08:16.743 --> 01:08:20.747
Woman: Oh, you're great
what are you talking about?

01:08:20.747 --> 01:08:24.883
I love you, Mom.
Thank you.

01:08:24.883 --> 01:08:26.971
Kayla.

01:08:26.971 --> 01:08:56.783
♪♪

01:08:56.783 --> 01:08:58.308
[Screaming]

01:08:58.308 --> 01:09:06.316
♪♪

01:09:06.316 --> 01:09:09.145
What the fuck?

01:09:09.145 --> 01:09:12.756
♪♪

01:09:12.756 --> 01:09:15.977
Kayla!
Aaron!

01:09:22.767 --> 01:09:24.638
♪♪

01:09:24.638 --> 01:09:33.604
[Laughter]

01:09:33.604 --> 01:09:35.301
Malik, oh, my God.

01:09:35.301 --> 01:09:36.563
I'm so glad you made it.

01:09:36.563 --> 01:09:39.218
It's such a special night.

01:09:39.218 --> 01:09:41.133
Malik:
What the fuck is this?
Where is she?

01:09:41.133 --> 01:09:44.354
She's fine. After all,
this is all for her.

01:09:44.354 --> 01:09:46.486
Aaron?
Aaron.

01:09:46.486 --> 01:09:49.750
[Laughter]

01:09:49.750 --> 01:09:51.317
Where have you been?

01:09:51.317 --> 01:09:52.536
What do you mean,
"Where have I been?"

01:09:52.536 --> 01:09:53.798
You kicked me out.

01:09:53.798 --> 01:09:56.627
That was
almost a week ago.

01:09:56.627 --> 01:09:59.630
Malik.

01:09:59.630 --> 01:10:04.461
Hey, welcome. I didn't know
you were going to be here.

01:10:04.461 --> 01:10:06.332
Where have you been?
-Malik what are you doing?

01:10:06.332 --> 01:10:08.421
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
Malik, no.

01:10:08.421 --> 01:10:10.858
Stop.

01:10:10.858 --> 01:10:13.383
Malik, Malik.
What are you doing?

01:10:13.383 --> 01:10:16.342
-I'm protecting her.
-From who?

01:10:16.342 --> 01:10:18.039
You!

01:10:18.039 --> 01:10:20.477
[Gunshot]

01:11:20.276 --> 01:11:28.458
♪♪

01:11:28.458 --> 01:11:32.462
[Prison door slams]

01:11:44.996 --> 01:11:47.694
Aaron:

01:11:47.694 --> 01:11:50.262
Malik.

01:11:52.438 --> 01:11:54.222
I'm putting the house
up for sale.

01:11:58.444 --> 01:11:59.837
Kayla and I...

01:12:01.273 --> 01:12:03.406
...we're going to move back to
the city

01:12:03.406 --> 01:12:06.104
and stay with my mother.
-Oh, my God, thank God.

01:12:06.104 --> 01:12:09.499
Oh, my God.

01:12:09.499 --> 01:12:14.373
Aaron, you have to run as far
away from this town as possible.

01:12:14.373 --> 01:12:16.767
It's not the town we're
running from, Malik.

01:12:24.470 --> 01:12:31.303
I know you don't understand it,
but I did what I had to do.

01:12:34.350 --> 01:12:37.091
Liam knows
why I had to do it.

01:12:37.091 --> 01:12:40.704
Liam?

01:12:40.704 --> 01:12:42.358
Who's Liam, Malik?

01:12:45.056 --> 01:12:48.668
My ex-boyfriend,
who do you think?

01:12:48.668 --> 01:12:50.278
Jesus Christ.

01:12:53.412 --> 01:12:56.937
Maybe if you just -- maybe
if you just go talk to him.

01:12:56.937 --> 01:12:59.244
Maybe If you talk to him, then
he can tell you everything

01:12:59.244 --> 01:13:03.596
and you'll know --
you'll know why I did it.

01:13:03.596 --> 01:13:06.164
I can't do that,
Malik.

01:13:06.164 --> 01:13:09.341
Why?

01:13:09.341 --> 01:13:10.951
Why can't you?

01:13:10.951 --> 01:13:18.002
♪♪

01:13:18.002 --> 01:13:21.788
-I have to go.
-No.

01:13:21.788 --> 01:13:25.096
No, Aaron,
please.

01:13:25.096 --> 01:13:27.620
Aaron, don't go --
just talk to him.

01:13:27.620 --> 01:13:29.622
Just talk to him,
please.

01:13:29.622 --> 01:13:32.538
Aaron, just talk to him.
I was just protecting her.

01:13:32.538 --> 01:13:38.675
[Sobbing]
I had no choice.

01:13:38.675 --> 01:14:44.392
♪♪

01:15:00.626 --> 01:15:03.629
Can I come in?

01:15:03.629 --> 01:15:08.286
[Crying]

01:15:22.300 --> 01:15:23.954
We're in this together.

01:15:27.610 --> 01:15:29.437
You know that,
right?

01:15:29.437 --> 01:15:32.005
We're gonna
get through this.

01:15:32.005 --> 01:15:35.356
[Crying]

01:16:26.233 --> 01:16:33.414
♪♪

01:16:33.414 --> 01:16:34.894
Woman: Is this
thing even working?

01:16:34.894 --> 01:16:37.331
Mom, seriously, the red light
is blinking,

01:16:37.331 --> 01:16:39.595
that means it's recording.

01:16:39.595 --> 01:16:41.597
What, it's a party.

01:16:41.597 --> 01:16:43.120
Come on, I want to go see Ty.

01:16:43.120 --> 01:16:44.817
You're too young
for a boyfriend.

01:16:47.646 --> 01:16:50.780
Marshall: You got broken into
in this town?

01:16:50.780 --> 01:16:55.132
Woman:
That's what we thought, my wife
is, she's really upset about it.

01:16:55.132 --> 01:16:58.135
Marshall: Well, obviously it
must have been teenagers.

01:16:58.135 --> 01:17:00.093
Woman: Well, speaking of which,
ours seem to be

01:17:00.093 --> 01:17:01.834
getting along just fine.

01:17:01.834 --> 01:17:05.490
Why don't you and Ty
come get a plate of food?

01:17:05.490 --> 01:17:07.100
Aaron: Jesus Christ.

01:17:07.100 --> 01:17:19.635
♪♪

01:17:43.528 --> 01:17:46.487
What the fuck are you?

01:17:46.487 --> 01:17:51.449
I'm someone who's been around
for a very long time.

01:17:51.449 --> 01:17:54.321
Kayla?

01:17:54.321 --> 01:17:55.758
[Door knocking]

01:17:58.848 --> 01:18:00.197
Kayla.

01:18:00.197 --> 01:18:03.287
I don't like this
any more then you.

01:18:03.287 --> 01:18:04.984
But this is how it works.

01:18:07.030 --> 01:18:12.339
And this, well, this,
is how we make it work.

01:18:12.339 --> 01:18:14.559
You can take me, okay?
You can take me.

01:18:14.559 --> 01:18:16.866
I'll do anything you want,
just don't hurt her.

01:18:16.866 --> 01:18:20.347
You know I can't do that.
It's too late.

01:18:20.347 --> 01:18:23.220
Stay the fuck
away from her!

01:18:23.220 --> 01:18:25.744
Kayla, open the door.

01:18:25.744 --> 01:18:27.833
Kayla, open the door, wake up.

01:18:27.833 --> 01:18:57.994
♪♪

01:18:57.994 --> 01:19:02.389
You broke out of jail
tonight, Malik.

01:19:02.389 --> 01:19:06.176
You had drugs in your system,
another relapse.

01:19:10.963 --> 01:19:16.186
You killed her, you killed your
husband, and then yourself.

01:19:16.186 --> 01:19:30.200
♪♪

01:19:30.200 --> 01:19:35.509
[Crying]
No.

01:19:35.509 --> 01:19:40.253
♪♪

01:19:40.253 --> 01:19:42.255
Why!?
-Isn't it beautiful?

01:19:45.693 --> 01:19:48.827
That's what everybody's
going to say,

01:19:48.827 --> 01:19:55.442
and not one soul will question
it because of who you are.

01:19:55.442 --> 01:19:57.662
People won't care,
Malik,

01:19:57.662 --> 01:20:01.231
they've already
got their minds made up.

01:20:01.231 --> 01:20:05.757
They're afraid of you,
and when the tides change,

01:20:05.757 --> 01:20:09.369
there will be someone
else to be afraid of.

01:20:09.369 --> 01:20:13.112
There always is,
there always will be.

01:20:15.636 --> 01:20:18.683
It's human nature --
fear.

01:20:18.683 --> 01:20:21.251
We just exploit it.

01:20:21.251 --> 01:20:28.301
♪♪

01:20:28.301 --> 01:20:40.792
[Whistling "When the Saints
Go Marching In"]

01:21:22.529 --> 01:21:40.417
♪♪

01:21:40.417 --> 01:21:43.028
Malik: <i>They choose someone
vulnerable,</i>

01:21:43.028 --> 01:21:45.117
<i>and they vilify them.</i>

01:21:45.117 --> 01:21:55.606
♪♪

01:21:55.606 --> 01:21:58.652
<i>They do this so no one bats
an eye.</i>

01:21:58.652 --> 01:22:02.918
♪♪

01:22:02.918 --> 01:22:06.182
<i>This happened to us
our first night living there.</i>

01:22:06.182 --> 01:22:08.619
<i>Everything I know
about this town</i>

01:22:08.619 --> 01:22:10.447
<i>and what the people here have
been doing,</i>

01:22:10.447 --> 01:22:12.318
<i>is in this document.</i>

01:22:12.318 --> 01:22:28.552
♪♪

01:22:28.552 --> 01:22:32.556
<i>I'm making this for you
so that you have a chance.</i>

01:22:32.556 --> 01:22:48.746
♪♪

01:22:48.746 --> 01:22:51.879
<i>I don't know
who will find this,</i>

01:22:51.879 --> 01:22:54.882
<i>or what kind
of person you are.</i>

01:22:54.882 --> 01:22:58.495
♪♪

01:22:58.495 --> 01:23:02.803
<i>But my hope is that
you might be the one</i>

01:23:02.803 --> 01:23:04.762
<i>to finally break this cycle.</i>

01:23:04.762 --> 01:23:23.041
♪♪

01:23:23.041 --> 01:23:25.174
<i>Now that I've told you all
this,</i>

01:23:25.174 --> 01:23:28.133
<i>what you do with the
information is up to you.</i>

01:23:31.136 --> 01:23:35.662
<i>Just remember, hope is never
silent.</i>

01:23:45.498 --> 01:26:53.077
♪♪
